result.execSummary:
The defendant Lauren A. FREE was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Forgery-Writings or Objects, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(1)(a).
  • Forgery-Uttering, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Minutes.

Stipulation and Order to Amend Criminal Bond.
It is hereby ordered that Ms. Free's cash bond in the above referenced case be modified from a $150.00 cash bond to a $150.00 signature bond with the conditions of that bond being that she 1) maintain absolute sobriety with the exception of any prescribed medications taken in their prescribed dosages; 2) reside at the Nova House and participate in their treatment program; 3) sign an authorization allowing the State to verify her location with Nova; and 4) that upon either voluntarily leaving the program or being terminated from the program, that Ms. Free would report back to the Manitowoc County Jail and her bond would be converted back into a cash bond.
Philip Hoff, through Public Defender.
